<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/52966326-jack-vasen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1456179595i/52966326._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/52966326-jack-vasen">Jack Vasen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I have been wondering about this myself. This may well be an allegory.<br/><br/>I hesitate to relate Arthur directly to Jesus since Jesu is a character in the o<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I have been wondering about this myself. This may well be an allegory.<br /><br />I hesitate to relate Arthur directly to Jesus since Jesu is a character in the ongoing story. However, I can see a relationship between Arthur's Summer Kingdom and Christ's ultimate kingdom.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
