        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer134651000" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7860136048862028906">Great ending to a fun series. This was probably my favorite book in this series as most of the characters were quite familiar to me (from King Arther and Queen Gwenhwyvar to Merlin of course). The book is a tale of Arthur uniting the British &quot;Summer Kingdom&quot; together and so there is a lot of battles and war. All the same, I quite enjoyed the story and was very impressed overall with Stephen Lawhead&apos;s ability to tell this story and his knowledge of the British legends. I plan to read more from hi</span>
  <span id="freeText7860136048862028906" style="display:none">Great ending to a fun series. This was probably my favorite book in this series as most of the characters were quite familiar to me (from King Arther and Queen Gwenhwyvar to Merlin of course). The book is a tale of Arthur uniting the British "Summer Kingdom" together and so there is a lot of battles and war. All the same, I quite enjoyed the story and was very impressed overall with Stephen Lawhead's ability to tell this story and his knowledge of the British legends. I plan to read more from him.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7860136048862028906" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
